Ponale Hydroelectric Power Plant (Italian: Centrale idroelettrica del Ponale) is a pumped storage plant, located in city of Riva del Garda in the Italian province of Trentino, on River Ponale between Lake Ledro and Lake Garda.
The station was built in 1928-1929 and underwent overhaul in 1998.
The station is known by the world record in high-rise concrete pumping during the reconstruction in 1994. The achieved record was 532m.
During construction of the plant, there was discovered the remains of a Bronze Age pile-dwelling village (over 10 000 piles) on the east of the Lake Ledro.
